<Layout
  title="High-End Washing Machine Repair | (424) 499-7788"
  description="High-end washing machine repair for Miele, ASKO, Bosch, Fisher & Paykel, Gaggenau, and Smeg washers in Los Angeles County, Orange County, and Ventura County."
  structuredData={structuredData}
  ogImage="/washer/washing-machine-repair-services.webp"
>
  <ParallaxHeader client:idle />

  <div
    class="maincontent"
    id="webpage"
  >
    <h2>
      High-End &amp; Luxury Washing Machine Repair – Professional &amp; Reliable
    </h2>

    <p>
      At <strong>Luxury Appliance Repair by Zaricci</strong>, we specialize in
      professional <strong>high-end washing machine repair</strong> for
      <strong> Miele, ASKO, Bosch, Fisher &amp; Paykel, and Smeg washers</strong>.
      Our technicians combine careful diagnostics with white-glove service to
      restore reliable washing performance while working respectfully around
      your laundry room, custom cabinetry, flooring, stacked appliances, and
      surrounding finishes.
    </p>

    <p>
      Today’s premium washing machines are designed with advanced sensors,
      electronic controls, specialized wash programs, high-speed spin cycles,
      water-management systems, smart features, and compact European
      installations. When a luxury washer begins leaking, stops draining, fails
      to spin correctly, or displays an error code, accurate diagnosis matters.
      Our technicians inspect the complete system before recommending the most
      appropriate repair.
    </p>

    <h2>
      European, Compact &amp; Smart Washing Machine Repair
    </h2>

    <p>
      European and high-end washing machines are often engineered differently
      from standard residential washers. Many models feature compact front-load
      designs, stacked installations, drain filters, recirculation systems,
      automatic detergent dispensing, water-level sensors, door-lock systems,
      high-speed spin cycles, smart controls, and model-specific electronics.
      At <strong>Luxury Appliance Repair by Zaricci</strong>, we provide
      specialized repair for premium washing machines from Miele, ASKO, Bosch,
      Fisher &amp; Paykel, and Smeg. See below for common issues we diagnose and
      repair for each brand.
    </p>
  </div>

  <Tabs1 client:visible />

  <div class="maincontent">
    <h2>
      What to Expect with Zaricci
    </h2>

    <ul>
      <li>
        Same-day luxury washing machine repair in most areas of Los Angeles,
        Ventura &amp; Orange County
      </li>

      <li>
        Experienced technicians familiar with premium, European, front-load,
        compact, stacked &amp; smart washing machine models
      </li>

      <li>
        Careful diagnostics for drainage, pump, filter, spin-cycle, vibration,
        gasket, door-lock, sensor, motor &amp; electronic-control issues
      </li>

      <li>
        Discreet service that respects your laundry room, cabinetry, flooring,
        stacked appliances &amp; schedule
      </li>

      <li>
        Follow-up support to help ensure your washing machine continues to
        perform reliably
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>
      Preventive Maintenance for High-End Washing Machines
    </h3>

    <p>
      Luxury and European washing machines are an investment. We offer
      preventive maintenance services designed to preserve washing performance,
      reduce the risk of drainage problems, help prevent leaks, support stable
      spin cycles, extend appliance lifespan, and reduce the likelihood of
      costly breakdowns.
    </p>

    <p>
      Depending on the model, washing machine maintenance may include inspection
      of the drain filter, pump, hoses, water connections, detergent dispenser,
      door gasket, door-lock system, suspension components, leveling, sensors,
      drum condition, and electronic controls. For compact or stacked laundry
      installations, we also inspect access limitations and surrounding
      clearances that may affect operation and future service.
    </p>

    <h2>
      Washing Machine Repair in Los Angeles, Orange County &amp; Ventura County
    </h2>

    <p>
      We service high-end washing machines in custom homes, hillside estates,
      coastal residences, luxury condos, and designer laundry rooms throughout
      Los Angeles County, Orange County, and Ventura County. Many of these homes
      feature compact European washing machines, front-load washers, stacked
      washer-dryer systems, premium laundry appliances, direct-drain
      connections, specialized water hookups, integrated smart controls, and
      custom cabinetry that require careful diagnostics, precise repair work,
      and clean, respectful service inside the home.
    </p>

    <h2>
      Common High-End Washing Machine Problems We Repair
    </h2>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Washing machine not draining:</strong> We inspect the drain
        filter, pump, drain hose, internal hoses, water-management system, and
        electronic controls.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Washing machine not spinning:</strong> We diagnose motor,
        suspension, drum, door-lock, sensor, balance-detection, and
        control-related issues.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Washing machine leaking:</strong> We inspect the door gasket,
        hoses, pump, water connections, detergent dispenser, seals, and
        appliance leveling.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Excessive vibration or loud operation:</strong> We check
        leveling, installation stability, shock absorbers, suspension
        components, drum movement, load-balance concerns, and internal wear.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Door not locking or opening correctly:</strong> We diagnose the
        door latch, lock mechanism, gasket, alignment, wiring, and related
        electronic controls.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Washer stopping during the cycle:</strong> We inspect drainage,
        water supply, sensors, motor operation, door-lock response, error codes,
        and electronic controls.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Washer not filling properly:</strong> We examine water inlet
        valves, hoses, filters, water pressure, sensors, and control-related
        concerns.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Detergent dispenser problems:</strong> We inspect dispenser
        components, automatic detergent-dosing systems where applicable,
        buildup, water flow, hoses, and model-specific controls.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Error codes or display issues:</strong> We use the appliance
        model and symptoms to trace sensor faults, wiring problems, control-board
        issues, and smart-feature concerns.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>
      Areas We Serve for Washing Machine Repair
    </h2>
  </div>

  <Areas client:visible />
</Layout>